Privacy Policy for XPer Discord Bot
Effective Date: 19/12/2024

XPer Discord Bot (hereinafter referred to as "the Bot") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information.

1. Data Collection
1.1 The Bot collects minimal data necessary for its core functionality, including:
- User IDs
- Server IDs
- Message activity (e.g., message counts)
1.2 No sensitive or personally identifiable information is collected.

2. Data Storage
2.1 All data is stored securely on encrypted servers.
2.2 Data retention is limited to active servers using the Bot. When the Bot is removed, associated data is deleted.

3. Data Sharing
3.1 The Bot does not share data with third parties.
3.2 Aggregated, non-identifiable data may be used for performance analytics or improvements.

4. User Rights
4.1 Users can request data deletion by contacting the Bot owner or server administrator.
4.2 Users may also request details about the data collected by the Bot.

5. Changes to the Policy
5.1 Updates to this Privacy Policy will be posted, and users will be notified in the Botâ€™s official server.

6. Contact
For questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact: https://discord.com/invite/tr55DGHEwN.
